<article>
	<p>This was an experimental horse done in three layers of paper (with foil as the inner one).  It was effective, but had problems as the layers needed to be done with a thinner paper to allow the outlines to be cut simultaneously, and this resulted in a weaker construction.  In this particular one the outer layer was done with a weak paper, so had little structural strength.  Despite the interesting effects possible, Robin decided that this wasn't worth much further work.</p>
