</div>
<p>I don't intend to disassemble and reconstruct this horse, as the paper is a bit fragile, and it would reveal no new principles.  This was a relatively early piece as later Robin formalized the interior cutting of patterns so that only unicorns would have a decorative motif cut into their outer layer.  Except, of course, when she changed her mind, which she was apt to do if requested.</p>
